I visited your studio with my sister. I had my acrylic nails refilled, and my sister got gel nails. Unfortunately, neither of them lasted even a week. However, the staff who served us were very friendly.  About eight days later, I returned to have the nails removed and expressed my dissatisfaction. There was hardly any response from the supervisors. I felt like they were avoiding addressing my concerns.  When another employee started to remove my nails, even she admitted that they were not stable. When I asked what else could be done, she only offered to remove them.  So, I ended up paying around 3,000 Indian Rupees for nails that didn‚Äôt even last a week, and an additional 900 Rupees to have them removed.  Dear Nail's Beyond Management, I understand that sometimes things don‚Äôt go as planned, but the way you handled the situation was completely unprofessional.
